casebody.data:
Wednesday, September 20, 2000

MERIT DOCKET

00-627. Westside Cellular, Inc. v. Pub. Util. Comm.

Public Utilities Commission, No. 97-1700-TP-COI. On motion for leave to intervene by the Ameritech Entities, motion to dismiss, and motion for leave to intervene by Verizon Wireless. Motion to dismiss sustained. Cause dismissed.

Moyer, C.J., Douglas, F.E. Sweeney, Cook and Lundberg Stratton, JJ., concur. Pfeifer, J., dissents, would deny the motion to dismiss, and would grant the motions for leave to intervene. Resnicic, J., not participating.
